            <section id="overview" class="section active">
                <h2>üìñ Course Overview</h2>
                <p>Managers need to know how to manage diverse distributed computing environments and leverage the opportunities these architectures provide. This course explores integration of data, users, graphics, and telephony through client/server and N-Tier service-oriented architectures, Internet, intranet/extranet, groupware, mobile, cloud, and other technologies.</p>
                
                <h3>What You'll Learn</h3>
                <p>This elective course reviews state-of-the-art technologies in software and hardware arenas while emphasizing management models and higher-level analysis. You'll complete practical projects that provide real-world opportunities to use tools that enhance work and build productivity.</p>

                <h3>üìï Required Textbook</h3>
                <div class="info-card">
                    <p><strong>Web Services, Service-Oriented Architectures, and Cloud Computing</strong></p>
                    <p>By Douglas K. Barry | 2nd Edition (2013)</p>
                    <p>Publisher: Elsevier | ISBN: 9780123983572</p>
                    <p style="margin-top: 15px; color: #764ba2;"><strong>üì¶ First Day¬Æ Inclusive Access:</strong> Digital materials available through D2L at a discounted price. Charged as a course fee after the drop date.</p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section id="objectives" class="section">
                <h2>üéØ Learning Objectives</h2>
                <p><strong>Competence Statement:</strong> Knows the basic principles of distributed computing, the process of systems development and structured methodologies, and understands the system life cycle. Can perform required functions at an introductory level.</p>
                
                <div class="objectives-grid">
                    <div class="objective-card">
                        <h3>üåê Distributed Systems</h3>
                        <p>Describe the concept of information and distributed systems, understanding unique architectural challenges.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="objective-card">
                        <h3>üìä Architecture Trends</h3>
                        <p>Discuss trends in distributed systems architecture and service-oriented design patterns.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="objective-card">
                        <h3>‚òÅÔ∏è Web Services & SOA</h3>
                        <p>Explain and implement concepts of Web Services and Service Oriented Architecture.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="objective-card">
                        <h3>üîß Cloud Computing</h3>
                        <p>Explain principles of cloud computing and modern distributed architectures.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="objective-card">
                        <h3>üîÑ Change Management</h3>
                        <p>Implement principles of managing change in modernization projects.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="objective-card">
                        <h3>ü§ñ AI Applications</h3>
                        <p>Understand AI in business applications and its implications for distributed systems.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

