            <section id="policies" class="section">
                <h2>üìã Course Policies</h2>
                
                <h3>‚è∞ Late Policy</h3>
                <div class="highlight-box">
                    <p><strong>Important:</strong> Late work causes delays for everyone and will only be accepted under limited circumstances:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>On-Time is On-Time:</strong> Submit by deadline through D2L. Technology issues are not an excuse.</li>
                        <li><strong>Without Approval:</strong> Missed deadlines without prior approval = zero (0) grade.</li>
                        <li><strong>Need Extension?</strong> Contact instructor at least 24 hours before due date with valid reason. Documentation may be required.</li>
                        <li><strong>Approved Late Work:</strong> May be submitted within 48 hours but loses 20% of total points unless documented emergency.</li>
                        <li><strong>Beyond 48 Hours:</strong> Work will not be accepted and receives a zero.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <h3>üéì Academic Integrity</h3>
                <p>The University does not accept plagiarism or collusion with other students unless permitted by instructor (e.g., group projects).</p>
                
                <div class="highlight-box">
                    <p><strong>Plagiarism Policy:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>First Offense:</strong> One-time opportunity to redo assignment with up to 50% point reduction.</li>
                        <li><strong>Second Offense:</strong> Assignment receives zero (0) grade.</li>
                        <li><strong>Repeated Plagiarism:</strong> Course failure will result.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <h3>ü§ñ Generative AI Policy</h3>
                <p>Generative AI tools (e.g., ChatGPT) may be used for any assignment with <strong>appropriate citation</strong>. Students are responsible for:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Fact-checking AI-generated statements</li>
                    <li>Evaluating validity of cited sources</li>
                    <li>Understanding that AI works better for some tasks than others</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>üë• Attendance</h3>
                <p>This is an online, asynchronous course that is <strong>not self-paced</strong>. Attendance is tracked by completion of assignments by stated due dates. If you don't complete work in the first two weeks, you will be automatically dropped.</p>

                <h3>‚ôø Accessibility</h3>
                <p>Students requesting accommodations must register with Disability Services at (651) 793-1549 as early as possible.</p>
            </section>

